{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"efdb2ac6-5f38-4970-aea5-155db5a5c52e","content":"There are no files in the working directory, so I'll walk you through the conversion with concrete examples.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML page:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\"\n                     Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only structural change** is adding `xmlns:vm` and `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` at the page level. All `{Binding …}` expressions are now compiled against that type.\n\n**2. Catch errors at build time — add this to your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Emit warnings for broken bindings -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n  <!-- Optionally promote those warnings to errors -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is the diagnostic for binding-path mismatches. With this config, a typo like `{Binding Thme}` becomes a **build error** instead of a silent runtime failure.\n\n**Key points:**\n- `x:DataType` can be set on any element, not just the page root — useful if a child binds to a different type.\n- To **opt out** for one binding (e.g., a runtime-only context), use `x:DataType=\"\"` or `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` on that element.\n- Compiled bindings are faster at runtime (no reflection) and give you compile-time safety.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"11b4b8c9-16aa-4f51-9d1d-2c71f32a5858","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty - there are no existing files. The user is asking me to explain how to convert a MAUI page to use compiled bindings. Since there's no actual code to modify, I'll provide guidance with concrete examples based on their description.","outputTokens":736,"requestId":"F40E:2EB5E6:1F5206A:231A201:69E81962"},"id":"08833cac-86d0-4722-a746-300c318a557a","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:42:24.854Z","parentId":"bb34cb90-0046-4a01-826a-6996afa50e41"}
